LeetCode No. 53 Maximum Subarray

The idea is to keep track of the maximum subarray with last element nums[i]. There are two cases. Case 1ï¼šthe maximum subarray with last element nums[i-1] is positive (say S), 
then the maximum subarray with last element nums[i] should be equal to S + nums[i]. Case 2: the maximum subarray with last element nums[i-1] is non-positive, then the maximum 
subarray with last element nums[i] should be equal to nums[i]. 

class Solution {
public:
    int maxSubArray(vector<int>& nums) {
        int i = 0;
        int N = nums.size();
        int current_sum = 0, Max = nums[0];
        for(i=0;i<N;++i)
        {
            if(current_sum >= 0)
            {
                current_sum = current_sum + nums[i];
            }
            else
            {
                current_sum = nums[i];
            }
            if(Max < current_sum)
            {
                Max = current_sum;
            }
        }
        return Max;
    }
};
